svg.text: Before starting the laboratory work, all members of our team had successfully passed the safety and security training. While working, our lab members are constantly guided and supervised by our instructors. We strictly follow the norms and regulations of the Institute of Technology for experimental work. If the strain developed will later be used in industrial bioreactors, then we need to further consider the possible risks to humans and the environment.

The Atlantic cod trypsin has been previously used in biomedical studies (Gudmundsdóttir et al., 2013) and is reported as non-toxic (Gudmundsdóttir et al., 2013). It has shown promising efficiency in the SALSA degradation kinetic modeling (please, refer to the Modeling page). Trypsin’s normal working pH level, which is in a range 7-9 units, (Lam et al., 2012) differs significantly from the gastrointestinal acidic pH, which range is 1.0-2.5 units (Evans et al., 1988).
